description.plain: Elgin Baylor Lumpkin, better known by his stage name Ginuwine, is an American singer-songwriter and actor. Signed to Epic Records since the mid-1990s, Ginuwine had released a number of multi-platinum and platinum-selling albums and singles, becoming one of R&B’s top artists during the late 1990’s and early 2000’s. He formed a supergroup with H-Town and Playa.

songs.title: Pony

description.plain:
“Pony” is Ginuwine’s debut single, released 3 months prior to his debut LP Ginuwine… the Bachelor in August 1996. The song was a huge commercial and critical success and is considered as one of the greatest R&B songs.

It was also an important record for producer Timbaland as it became his first successful foray into R&B production, a genre he would have further success in with the likes of Aaliyah, Brandy and Justin Timberlake.

songs.title: Differences

description.plain:
From Ginuwine… The Bachelor to Ginuwine… the boyfriend. This classic is just an ode to that special someone.

Whoever she is, she has made a positive impact on G’s life.

The main message throughout the whole song is that he finally settled down and found that one person he wants to share his world with.

songs.title: So Anxious

description.plain:
“So Anxious” was released as the third single of 100% Ginuwine on June 1, 1999.

The lyrics describe a narrative who is “so anxious” for his lover to return his calls so they can meet up, as in, “meet up”.
